# AWS Credentials from 1Password
# See README.md for setup instructions
#
# To enable 1Password integration:
# 1. Create 1Password items: "AWS Personal" and/or "AWS Work"
# 2. Each item needs fields: access_key_id, secret_access_key
# 3. Uncomment and restore the template syntax below:
#
# EXAMPLE TEMPLATE SYNTAX (remove # and fix brackets):
#   { {- if (onepasswordItemFields "AWS Personal") } }
#   [default]
#   aws_access_key_id = { { (onepasswordItemFields "AWS Personal").access_key_id.value } }
#   aws_secret_access_key = { { (onepasswordItemFields "AWS Personal").secret_access_key.value } }
#   region = us-east-1
#   { {- end } }
#
# NOTE: Remove spaces inside curly brackets when enabling
# For now, add your credentials manually to ~/.aws/credentials if needed
